# Component Conventions

## File layout

One component per file. Filename PascalCase matches the export.

```
src/lib/components/
├── ui/                       # shadcn-svelte primitives (do not edit)
├── editor/
│   ├── Editor.svelte
│   ├── Toolbar.svelte
│   └── PresenceCursor.svelte
├── NoteList.svelte
└── NoteCard.svelte
```

## Props interface

Explicit `Props` interface in `<script lang="ts">`:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import type { Note } from '$lib/types';
  import { cn } from '$lib/cn';

  interface Props {
    note: Note;
    class?: string;
    onarchive?: (id: string) => void;
  }

  let { note, class: className = '', onarchive }: Props = $props();
</script>

<article class={cn('rounded-md border p-4', note.archivedAt && 'opacity-60', className)}>
  <h3>{note.title}</h3>
  <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">{note.body.slice(0, 200)}</p>
  {#if onarchive}
    <button type="button" onclick={() => onarchive(note.id)}>Archive</button>
  {/if}
</article>
```

## Rules

- Accept `class` prop (aliased to `className` in destructure) and merge with `cn()`
- Interactive elements are semantic (`<button>`, `<a>`), never `<div onclick>`
- Callback props named `on<event>` (lowercase)
- Keep component files under 150 lines — extract subcomponents when they grow

## Server interaction

You cannot call the database or a server function directly. Instead:

- **For data** — the page's load function provides it as `data` prop; destructure in `+page.svelte` and pass to components
- **For mutations** — use `use:enhance` on a `<form>` pointing at a named action

```svelte
<!-- +page.svelte (in routes, not components) -->
<script lang="ts">
  import { enhance } from '$app/forms';
  import NoteEditor from '$lib/components/NoteEditor.svelte';

  let { data, form } = $props();
</script>

<form method="POST" action="?/update" use:enhance>
  <NoteEditor initial={data.note} />
  <button type="submit">Save</button>
</form>

{#if form?.error}
  <p role="alert">{form.error}</p>
{/if}
```

## shadcn-svelte primitives

Do not edit anything in `src/lib/components/ui/`. Compose with them:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { Button } from '$lib/components/ui/button';
  import * as Dialog from '$lib/components/ui/dialog';
</script>

<Dialog.Root>
  <Dialog.Trigger asChild><Button>Share</Button></Dialog.Trigger>
  <Dialog.Content>
    <Dialog.Title>Share note</Dialog.Title>
    ...
  </Dialog.Content>
</Dialog.Root>
```

If you need a new primitive, add it via `pnpm dlx shadcn-svelte@latest add <name>`
and commit the generated files.

## Don't

- Don't import from `$lib/server/*` — it won't ship to the client; the build will fail
- Don't call `fetch()` directly — use `use:enhance` for forms, or `$app/forms`'s `applyAction` for imperative submissions
- Don't define UI types in `src/lib/types/` — keep those in the component file
- Don't use inline `style="…"` except for animation transforms
